 us to rethink the possibilities—and pitfalls—of using halfway houses to manage the worst excesses of mass incarceration. A portrait of life in the long shadow of the carceral state, Halfway House lets us see the struggles of reentry through the eyes of former prisoners.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAlternatives to imprisonmentzUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aCriminalsxRehabilitationzUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aHalfway houseszUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aPrisonersxDeinstitutionalizationzUnited StatesvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  aAddiction recovery.  aAlternatives to prison.  aAmerican dream.  aCarceral.  aCollaboration.  aCommunity college.  aCycle of confinement.  aDrug abstinence.  aDrug crisis.  aEducation.  aFamily reunification.  aFoucault.  aHealthcare.  aHeroin.  aInvisible punishment.  aLiminality.  aMass incarceration.  aNIMBY.  aPain management.  aPenal-welfarism.  aPrisoner families.  aReentry.  aSocial exclusion.  aSocial welfare.  aTwelve steps.  aWar on drugs.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073910740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479800711423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479800711/original  a978-3-11-073910-7  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-